      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OAKLEY SHARD NZ (1) is an in-form mare has put together four wins and two minor placings from six starts this prep. Kept the ball rolling last time when she led from wider and dug deep to score at this circuit and distance, getting home by a head. Can take full advantage of the ace draw to win again. REDS ABLAZE (6) drew on the back row and did some work so was far from disgraced when beaten just over 6m against the boys last week. Suited back in mares' grade having won two back at this circuit and distance. OHANA DANCER (3) draws well and could be close to another win after two successive placings here, the latest from the back row. Last-start placegetter MAJORITA JUJON (5) deserves respect off a win from this barrier here two back.",
